      (c.id, 'CAT1-E0006', 'Catertherm', '122270-ZK', 'Catertherm Food Transport - K180 ECO Cooling. Guides: 12 x GN1/1, 80mm spacing. Outer: W: 525mm x D: 770mm x H: 1575mm. Inner: W: 330mm x D: 540mm x H: 1000mm. Weight: 77 kg. Power: 230V/190W. Temperature Range: 3C - 20C. One Grip Handle. Additional Pull Handles On The Sides Are Included Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour', 3726.54, 0.00, '1225-035', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'CAT14-E0001', 'Catertherm', 'Model IO', 'Decorative Heat Lamp Focus Shade Model - IO Material: Anodised aluminium, galvanised steel. Shade Dimensions: H 250mm / D 220mm. Switch position - Shade Colour: Black, Aluminum and Racing Green (TO BE ADVISED AT TIME OF ORDER) Heat Lamp Cord - Straight Retractable (Ordered With Lamp).Retractable Mechanism, With Straight Cord. Cord length - Min 550 mm - Max 2000mm. To be confirmed. Heat Source: Philips infrared lamp (included), 2700K 250W. Warranty - Two years parts and labour', 479.60, 0.00, '0825-039', 'Aug 2025'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E0012', 'Catertherm', 'BM2100W', 'Drop-in electric 3 x 1/1GN Hot well unit, to hold hot food. Dry well or wet well with drainage tap. Temperature – Adjustable in 1°C increments from ambient to +140° C (at an ambient temperature of +22° C) Installation Height – 105mm Cut out size – 1060mm x 580mm Electrical Rating – 240v 2340w 50/60 Hz Certifications – CE Approved, UL & NSF Approval Pending Cleaning – Unit must be cleaned with Anti-bacterial cleaner Controller – Digital temperature controller with 1m cable as standard (longer cable available) Power Cable – 2m long with UK plug as standard (other plugs available on request) Warranty - One year parts and labour', 4439.77, 40.00, '1225-060', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E0011', 'Catertherm', 'JH2100K', 'Drop-in electric 3x1/1 GN sized Cold plate unit, to hold cold food Temperature – Adjustable from ambient to -5° (at an ambient temperature of +22° C) Installation Height – 200mm Cut out size – 1000mm x 540mm x 160mm (depending on counter material) Surface – Stainless Steel Electrical Rating – 240v 100w 50/60 Hz Certifications – CE Approved, UL & NSF Approval Pending Ventilation Requirements – Fresh air intake and hot air escape must be ensured (can be ducted to operator side of counter, please installation considerations for information) Cleaning – Unit to be cleaned with anti-bacterial cleaner, silicone to be cleaned Controller – Digital temperature controller with 1m cable as standard (longer cable available) Power Cable – 2m long with UK plug as standard Warranty - One year parts and la', 4943.00, 40.00, '1225-060', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00024', 'Catertherm', 'JH1400K/W-EC', 'GN2/1 Hot & Cold Plate (Counter Drop-In) - JH1400K/W-EC. 660mm x 530mm x 190mm deep (under counter). Bare Aluminium Top Surface. 1500w 230v (6.52A) 50/60Hz, Controllable between -5C and +140C. R600a coolant, Built in refrigeration and heating system. Ready to plug in with standard UK 13A plug. Weight 23KG. Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour Price includes: 2No. 2nd Hot & Cold Plate 2No. - Laminam for GN2/1 Unit 2No.- Install Kit for GN2/1 Unit 1No. F90U Convection Heat', 4492.14, 40.00, '0526-022', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E0005', 'Catertherm', 'JH2100K/W-EC', 'GN3/1 Hot & Cold Plate (Counter Drop-In)', 1404.18, 0.00, '0126-024', 'Jan 2026'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00019', 'Catertherm', 'JH2100W', 'GN3/1 Hot Plate (Counter Drop-In) 990mm x 530mm x 80mm deep (Counter Drop In). Top surface as per next line. 1500w 230v (6.52A) 50/60Hz, Controllable between 22C and +140C. Ready to plug in with standard UK 13A plug. Weight 20KG. Nett Weight - 15kg. Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour Price includes for black glass and 1No. installation kit.', 2340.30, 40.00, '0226-078', 'Feb 2026'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00017', 'Catertherm', 'VL1-RS-SRK', 'Heat Lamp Focus RS, Standard Cord, Copper - VL1-RS-SRK. Model RS, Standard Cord, Colour: Copper. Straight Retractable Length: Standard (Min 0mm / Max 1300mm). Material: Anodised aluminium, galvanised steel. Shade Dimensions: H 220mm / D 220mm. Heat Source: Philips infrared lamp (included), 2700K 250W. Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour', 663.00, 40.00, '0226-056', 'Feb 2026'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00018', 'Catertherm', '1224-TOPIK', 'Heat Lamp Trattoria 1224, Standard Cord, Copper - 1224-TOPIK. Model Trattoria 1224, Standard Cord, Colour: Copper. Straight Retractable Length: Standard (Min 0mm / Max 1300mm).Material: Anodised aluminium, galvanised steel. Shade Dimensions: H 330mm / D 280mm. Heat Source: Philips infrared lamp (included), 2700K 250W. Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour', 570.00, 40.00, '0226-056', 'Feb 2026'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00016', 'Catertherm', '412', 'Hot Tray Focus - 412 - Stainless Steel, GN Standard - Adapted to 2x GN 1/1. Power / Voltage - 1800w / 230v. Control - Dial on front. Material - Stainless Steel. IP Rating - IP43. Temperature - Max 105C. Dimensions: 1200mm(w) x 400mm(d) x 53mm(h) Warranty: 2 Years Parts & Labour', 966.50, 0.00, '0126-024', 'Jan 2026'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E0011-AC', 'Catertherm', 'Install kit', 'Install Kit for GN3/1 Unit', 166.40, 40.00, '1225-060', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00014', 'Catertherm', '1224-TOPIM-SR', 'Model 1224 Trattoria, Straight Retractable Cord, Colour: Brass. Retractable Length: Standard (Min 0 mm / Max 1300 mm). Shade Dimensions: H 330mm / D 280mm. Heat Source: Philips infrared lamp (included), 2700K 375W. Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour', 570.00, 40.00, '1225-084', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'CAT1-E00015', 'Catertherm', 'VL1-RO-SRM', 'Model RO, Straight Retractable Cord, Colour: Brass. Retractable Length: Standard (Min 0 mm / Max 1300 mm). Heat Source: Philips infrared lamp (included), 2700K 375W. Shade Dimensions: H 330mm / D 280mm. Warranty: 2 Years Parts and Labour', 682.00, 40.00, '1225-086', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'GAS1-00013', 'CCE', 'FZB003', 'EX DEMO UNIT - Blast Chiller 3 x 1/1 GN chills 12 kg of food from +70°C to +3°C in 90 minutes and freezes 8 kg from +70°C to -18°C in 240 minutes. 13 amp Dimensions: 750mm W x 740mm D x 730mm H No Warranty', 1500.00, 50.00, '0425-088', 'Apr 2025'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT DISPOSAL', 'CCE', 'DISPOSAL', 'Remove From a Kerbside Location for safe disposal 1No. existing redundant Fridge equipment. “To employ suitably competent and qualified engineers to undertake the recovering, recycling, reclaiming or disposal of Controlled substances (Ozone-Depleting Substances) in line with The Environmental Protection Regulations (Controls on Ozone-Depleting Substances) SI 2011/1543, Regulation (EC) 1005/2009.', 350.00, 0.00, '0226-015', 'Feb 2026'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-350', 'CCE London', 'DRW-OM', 'Drawing/O&M Manual', 100.00, 0.00, '0426-016', 'Apr 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT EXTEND', 'CCE London', 'Extended Warranty', 'Extra 2 Years Warranty Supplied by CCE (4 Years in Total) Free of Charge', 0.00, 0.00, '0526-003', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT INCLU', 'CCE London', 'FREE TEXT INCLUDED', 'INCLUDED IN ITEM NO.', 0.00, 0.00, '1125-063', 'Nov 2025'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-100', 'CCE London', 'BULL', 'Labour factory bullnose edge', 138.00, 35.00, '1225-003', 'Dec 2025'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-004', 'CCE London', 'DEL-SECTIONS', 'Labour factory deliver in sections', 92.00, 35.00, '0526-021', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-170', 'CCE London', 'FIT-DWTROLL', 'Labour factory fit dwt rollers', 46.00, 35.00, '0426-024', 'Apr 2026'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-105', 'CCE London', 'BURNISH', 'Labour factory metal finish burnished', 92.00, 35.00, '0526-021', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-110', 'CCE London', 'MIRROR-DT', 'Labour factory metal finish mirror polished', 184.00, 35.00, '0526-021', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-001', 'CCE London', 'NWH', 'Labour factory NWH', 92.00, 35.00, '0526-021', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'LABOUR-050', 'CCE London', 'WIRE', 'Labour factory wire socket', 46.00, 35.00, '0526-021', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT2', 'CCE London', 'DELIVERY', 'Price includes a standard kerbside delivery (NON-TIMED) direct to site to a suitable drop-off location during normal working hours on a weekday when the manufacturer’s transport is in the local area. See Delivery Notes below.', 0.00, 0.00, '0526-016', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT PM', 'CCE London', 'Project Management', 'Project Management incorporating: - Provision of a Contracts Manager for the duration of the project. The Contracts Manager will be your point of contact for the project. The CM will liaise with other members of the project team to ensure all requirements for our extent of the project are covered ensuring a smooth operation / installation. - Collating and management of equipment at our secured and fully insured storage facility prior in readiness for delivery to site to achieve "just in time" deliveries to site. - Contract administration for the project, including Health and Safety, Operation and Maintenance manuals, and organising of training for staff - Liaison with other external contractors employed by the client (e.g. M & E Contractors) to ensure that on-site services, delivery times ', 150.00, 0.00, '0526-023', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT SPARE NO.', 'CCE London', 'SPARE NO.', 'SPARE NO. HIDDEN MONEY TO MAKE UP TO £150 MINIMUM ORDER VALUE', 22.16, 0.00, '0526-007', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT3', 'CCE London', 'DEL-POS', 'To attend site during Early AM hours on a weekday to carry out a dedicated timed delivery of all equipment as quoted above (time to be confirmed and agreed with Client). Unit will then be taken from kerbside up to final position on rooftop to be plugged in and tested. All works to be carried out in one continuous operation in one site visit.', 240.00, 0.00, '1125-077', 'Nov 2025'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT1', 'CCE London', 'STRIP OUT / SITE WORKS', 'To attend site during normal working hours on a weekday to carry out the following in one continuous site-visit: A) Disconnect and reposition existing water filter onto the back wall and reinstate B) Disconnect and reposition existing upright ice machine up to the LHS wall and reinstate C) Cut front left leg and connecting box section of existing bench, creating void for counter ice machine D) Disconnect and reposition existing counter ice machine from BOH Coral room to LG kitchen and reinstate in void under bench NOTE: We will reuse part of the off-cut of the existing fabrication to form additional support to the bench All works are to be carried out in accordance with the Site Works Specifications below.', 648.00, 0.00, '0526-023', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT ELEC', 'CCE London', 'Electrics', 'To attend site during normal working hours to run new 32 amp single phase power in upstairs back of house for new dishwasher. To supply & cut 2 no 500 x 500 hatches in plasterboard ceiling, installing wood around cut out for hatches to be secured. Price includes labour, materials, cable, breaker, isolator, hatches and wood, as well as additional materials for electrics for 6 grid combi oven in basement kitchen. All work to be carried out in accordance with the Site Work Specification below.', 800.00, 0.00, '1025-066', 'Oct 2025'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT4', 'CCE London', 'INSTALL', 'To attend site during normal working hours, to carry out the following in one continuous operation: A) Disconnect, strip out and remove for safe disposal of existing worktop and induction untis. B) Installation of new worktop. B) Deliver, position, install, test and commission the above quoted hot and cold plates All work to be carried out in accordance with the site works specification below.', 1650.00, 0.00, '0526-022', 'May 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT5', 'CCE London', 'FAB SITE WORK', 'To attend site in London to carry out the following refurbishment works to the existing Hot Pass:- A) To supply and fit 4no sliding hotcupboard doors complete with door rollers, sliding door track and bottom guides. B) To carry out alll re-wiring and supply and fit new controls with blown air fan system. C) To carry out necessary welding repairs to bottom valance. All works to take place outside of normal working hours (night work), including project management and pre-install checks. All works to be carried out in accordance with the Site Work Specification below.', 0.00, 0.00, '0226-074', 'Feb 2026'),
      (c.id, 'FREE TEXT DRAWING', 'CCE London', 'DRAWING', 'TO BE READ IN CONJUNCTION WITH CCE DRG No. 6063-GA REV E', 0.00, 0.00, '0226-024', 'Feb 2026');
